

Why prefer hibernate over jdbc;
   Hibernate eliminates a lot of boilerplate code that comes with jdbc.
   Hibernate supports inheritance association and collections.
   Hibernate implicitly provides transaction management!
   Hibernate wraps exceptions and throws JDBC Exceptions which are unchecked exceptions.





What is ORM Tool.
   ORM tool helps in simplifying data creation , manipulation and access.




Why you should use hibernate;

  1) Hibernate overcomes the database dependency faced in jdbc.
  2) Changing of database cost a lot when working with jdbc.
  3) code portability is easily handled.
  4) Strengthens the object level.
  5) it overcomes the exception-handling;





